One improvement I'd make

Instead of:

return null;

I'd ask the lead whether they want:

return ResponseEntity.noContent().build();

when no record exists. That's often cleaner than returning a 200 with a null body.

Before coding, check whether there is already a similar pattern in the preferences-api project (controller → service → repository). For a first Jira card, matching the existing code style is usually more important than using the most advanced pattern.






